Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.08,0:00:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everyone, Kaleido Star is going to start.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.19,0:00:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When you watch Kaleido Star, please \Nkeep your room brightly lit,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and sit as far from the TV as you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, well, well. What are you good at doing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.30,0:00:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Cooking? Participating \Nin sports? Or studying?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.67,0:00:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mia is very good at coming up \Nwith storylines and writing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm so excited to find out what kind \Nof story she is going to write.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's support our hard-working \NMia. Let's support! Let's support!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dare mo sagashiteru yume wa kitto aru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.02,0:00:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dokoka ni aru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:01:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Negai ga itsuka kanau made hitori ja nai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Saigo made yareru to ittetane {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.55,0:01:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kitto tsuyogatte itanda {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.90,0:01:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Itsudatte muchabakka de zutto karamawari de{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.56,0:01:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dakedo anata dake ga soba ni ita{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.95,0:01:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Daremo sagashiteru yume wa kitto aru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.91,0:01:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Arukidaseru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Koko kara nanika ga hajimaru {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.13,0:01:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shinjite itai {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.17,0:02:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mada minu hikari yakusoku \Nno basho e to tsuzuite yuku{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Negai ga itsuka kanau made hitori ja naisa{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One week...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.32,0:02:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make it so you can perform \Nthis on stage in one week.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.05,0:02:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.49,0:02:31.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Fire It Up! Amazing Mia."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.45,0:02:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a first step, come up with \Na tentative plan in three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In three days...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.07,0:02:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Mia!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.77,0:02:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's future is on your shoulders, Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.71,0:02:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have to pressure me like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying hard, but I can't write!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.96,0:02:53.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.93,0:02:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.50,0:03:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe this is impossible for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.66,0:03:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. Not at all. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not good at working under pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't write because you're trying to \Nwrite a masterpiece from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be yourself. Be yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'm a little too zealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.51,0:03:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also have to be careful that \Nwe don't say anything unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Telling you how much we're expecting \Nfrom you is not a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.01,0:03:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I think I should relax and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.02,0:03:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you write that fantastic masterpiece yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got so excited, I couldn't sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I brought you something to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a laughing matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, have a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.35,0:03:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, why does the \NBoss want me to correct this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what he wants from me when \Nhe just says, "Not good. Correct it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, he \Nalways just says "Do it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:03:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we played The Little Mermaid,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:04:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he just told Sora to create her own \Nlittle mermaid at the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.59,0:04:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd told her what needed to be done, \NSora wouldn't have suffered as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.66,0:04:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Miss Sarah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.99,0:04:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos has always been like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.74,0:04:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos has been like that since \Nhe started Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, in those days, he used to revise the \Ncontents of the performance every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.36,0:04:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the contents of the show \Nwere different every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.94,0:04:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since Kaleido Stage has grown so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,performing exactly the \Nsame show became ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, the way Kalos handles \Neverything has not changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.08,0:04:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take your Little Mermaid, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.88,0:04:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you based that character on what someone \Ntold you to do, how would you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you'd be as attached \Nto that character as you are now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.09,0:04:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... It could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe he just doesn't want \Nto think of it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.02,0:04:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do you already have a rough idea of \Nwhat kind of story you want to write?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.90,0:04:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the number of people we have,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking about writing \Nthat ghost love story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.32,0:05:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I think something is still missing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if we want to make it work onstage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.91,0:05:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may find a hint in the \Nmaterials in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.41,0:05:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this performance \Nusing the cloth pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.08,0:05:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to try this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.75,0:05:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I can do fire-breathing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.73,0:05:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Even though you're a diva?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I should try \Nsomething with a motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.42,0:05:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the performance we can \Ndo depends on who we have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does everyone really think that Yuri's \Ntheatrical company is that great?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the rumor,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,anyone who leaves Kaleido Stage
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can join his theatrical \Ncompany unconditionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we're too talented, and he's, \Nlike, afraid of asking us to join.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.16,0:05:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I think he, like, \Njust forgot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.99,0:05:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Mia! Go beyond Shakespeare!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Sarah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since Mia is working hard, \NI also have to work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleido Stage is not as \Ngreat a place as you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos has misled everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.29,0:06:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you're having \Na hard time sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you don't need to read Tarot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I know it will \Njust show something bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.12,0:06:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will sing a lullaby for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Then,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.33,0:06:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Lalalu, lalula, sleep, good girl. ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Lalula, lalalu, go on and... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:49.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,You sound creepy. I can't sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.09,0:06:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mia. You woke up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.35,0:07:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Sora?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.52,0:07:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She came here first thing in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and she went to the practice room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.02,0:07:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.02,0:07:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.60,0:07:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As of today, thirteen \Nmore people are leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.76,0:07:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora... Is she crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.98,0:07:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora! Sora!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.98,0:07:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Sora!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.84,0:07:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.28,0:07:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to try that by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.34,0:07:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you how to do it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.95,0:07:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, thirteen more people are quitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.77,0:07:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way things are going now,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.64,0:07:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we will end up having a little \Nover ten people left with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.43,0:07:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon Park!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.28,0:07:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please continue what you were saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already heard about Kaleido Stage's \Nsituation through the grapevine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.21,0:08:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos is ready to let an absolute amateur \Ntake charge of the next performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.50,0:08:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frankly, I'm disappointed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.19,0:08:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm asking you to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.42,0:08:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.13,0:08:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You accept that easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been interested in Kaleido \NStage for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.53,0:08:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know what \NKalos will say about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will persuade him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I thought you were a pretty cool woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.90,0:08:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please listen to me seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.07,0:08:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After three days, a tentative \Nplan will be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he sees that plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he'll have no choice but to \Nacknowledge what we have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we do something, Kaleido \NStage will be finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.09,0:08:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Naegino.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.26,0:08:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you have a seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:08:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.58,0:09:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy that you came here to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.48,0:09:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About that thing you were \Ntalking about the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I don't know what will \Nhappen to Kaleido Stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought maybe I should just cut \Nall ties, cleanly and completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.49,0:09:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,take care of everything once and \Nfor all and join your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.65,0:09:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, I still can't \Ndecide what I should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.10,0:09:18.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Your acting is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you want to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know why you are trying \Nto destroy Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to find out why...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.17,0:09:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you find out about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.18,0:09:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's what's going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.65,0:09:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri Killian is Arlon Brass' son.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.59,0:09:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that Killian is \Nhis mother's maiden name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri is trying to take revenge on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.70,0:09:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.05,0:10:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been waiting for this day to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.91,0:10:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was a trapeze artist like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he was also one of \NKaleido Stage's founders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.83,0:10:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kalos killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.38,0:10:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.31,0:10:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora, please come to my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.90,0:10:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't have a female top star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.39,0:10:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're qualified to be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.24,0:10:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, only about ten \Npeople are going to remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri... I really can't forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Mia?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this was when we had so many people...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.52,0:10:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.89,0:11:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about if the leading character of \Nthe ghost is the owner of a circus?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.22,0:11:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The protagonist became a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.47,0:11:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's alone, recalling a time \Nwhen the circus was cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this story can give everyone a \Nchance to show off their best talents!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the only person left by his side \Nis the woman who was his lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.32,0:11:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last scene is a touching farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says goodbye to the one he loves the most
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while he's lost in beautiful reminiscence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll make people cry. I \Nknow it'll make people cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a chance that this \Ncould be an amazing masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Mia!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may surpass Shakespeare!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.42,0:11:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as I expected, the things I \Nwas worried about came true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Mia is still an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.28,0:12:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the help of Simon Park's direction, \Nlet's re-create Cinderella.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have any objection, do you, Kalos?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Simon Park is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.81,0:12:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, everything is set, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.08,0:12:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia, you can leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.50,0:12:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next show will be directed \Nand produced by Mia Guillem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revise the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have four days until the deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.07,0:12:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just say we weren't meant \Nto work together this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should do dinner some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon Park!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.62,0:12:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to be a supervisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.28,0:12:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask you to support Mia Guillem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos, I think that is so rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It sounds interesting. I will do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.31,0:12:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.78,0:12:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have places to go, so \NI have to excuse myself now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:13:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Send the script to my address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.21,0:13:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for everything else, \Nplease talk to my agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Simon Park is going to support me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.94,0:13:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.24,0:13:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? That genius, Simon Park, \Nis going to read my script.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.87,0:13:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That itself makes me so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will strive to revise any \Ncorrections to perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.05,0:13:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should revise the parts I don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.76,0:13:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mia is making steady progress. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.72,0:13:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I shouldn't be feeling this way either.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.44,0:13:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}About Mr. Yuri...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think I should talk to the \NBoss and make sure of the truth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.40,0:14:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.75,0:14:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.69,0:14:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.89,0:14:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yuri said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.74,0:14:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.90,0:14:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalos forced my father \Nto do a risky maneuver.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he used my father's death for promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that investors at \Nthat time hid Arlon's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.41,0:14:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which actually led to the \Nrumor spreading more,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and our audience numbers increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.88,0:14:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I will tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arlon was the one who tried that \Nmaneuver, by his own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.47,0:14:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Mr. Yuri is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.74,0:14:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, Yuri also should know better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you force a person,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if that person is afraid of \Ndoing it, he never can jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kalos has been blaming \Nhimself for what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he stays silent, just \Nwatching what Yuri is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is something very hard to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.00,0:14:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your friends don't need to \Nworry about something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.91,0:15:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, you should only \Nfocus on your performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.63,0:15:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, could you please wait for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A call from Simon Park to Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.68,0:15:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you want me to delete pages 2 through 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you want me to delete \Nfrom the middle of page 5...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to page 24?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.18,0:15:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you want me to change the last scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.05,0:15:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's the scene when the protagonist \Nand his lover say good-bye, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. But we see this kind \Nof last scene all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.77,0:15:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To replace the sections we deleted, \Nwhy don't we do something fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And come up with a few more \Nhighlight scenes for the climax.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.05,0:15:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Take care...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.22,0:15:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, I need to rewrite it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:15:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will go to apologize to the Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.16,0:16:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.09,0:16:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will tell him, "Sorry, \Nbut I can't do this."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mia!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.43,0:16:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.76,0:16:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, if I continue and \Ncan't finish writing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will end up troubling you all. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.78,0:16:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.74,0:16:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say something so irresponsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I know Kalos never asks something \Nof someone who is not capable of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.99,0:16:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to write it, Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.26,0:16:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to give in to the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you make up your mind \Nsaying that you can't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.24,0:16:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that will be the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.99,0:16:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we did the Triple Illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.46,0:16:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought "we'll never \Nmake it" so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I even stepped down from the role once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.81,0:16:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'd rather perfect it with Anna and Sora."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.59,0:16:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that moment, I thought, "I \Nhave to do this no matter what."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.63,0:17:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, "No matter what, \NI'm going to perfect it."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was why I could push myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia, let's do this to the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't give up... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.50,0:17:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and do it to the last. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't give up... Don't give up...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A story about people who don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This could be a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.36,0:17:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.03,0:17:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The number of members decreased, \Nbut Kaleido Stage still exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.86,0:17:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this show becomes successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.53,0:17:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,some of the people who left \NKaleido Stage may come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I make this wish into \Na part of the story...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I think I can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I can gather everyone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.27,0:17:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.17,0:17:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, since we don't have that many people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.44,0:17:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each of you, please be ready to perform
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.09,0:18:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least three kinds of \Nroutines from your repertoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.10,0:18:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless I know the story, I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.59,0:18:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The script is not finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can she...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.59,0:18:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you finish writing the script?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.75,0:18:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will finish it. Absolutely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.40,0:18:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, everyone, let's start practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Wrap the cloth tight around your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.38,0:18:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll revise it so it \Nwill go in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Light B5 is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.57,0:18:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is working to create \Ntheir own performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we are back to \Nthe way we used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.87,0:18:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think you can still make it better?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.28,0:18:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.49,0:19:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about this kind of swing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.41,0:19:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also want to try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.99,0:19:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of everyone left in Kaleido Stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only person who is capable \Nof being my partner is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.50,0:19:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you say no, I'm \Nstill making you my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.64,0:19:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, it's almost perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.84,0:19:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we still have eight more \Nhours, we should do one more push.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make it so the whole cast's mood \Nbuilds up at once toward the last scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.81,0:19:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know conveying that kind of buildup to the \Naudience is Kaleido Stage's charm, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.60,0:19:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I will try.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.27,0:19:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.30,0:19:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have one favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.34,0:19:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:19:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shorten all female performers' skirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.61,0:19:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your script is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will raise the curtain for \Nopening day one week from today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start rehearsal immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.70,0:20:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stage is the world of fire and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a story about two groups of \Nyoung people fighting in that world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that scene, I want you \Nto perform more wildly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.95,0:20:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but, maybe it's okay the way \Nyou're doing it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct with confidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Originally, they were \Nfriends in the same group.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While young men fight each \Nother, they begin to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the director \Ngets new ideas every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a sceneman's worst nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.31,0:20:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jean, you're so alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, more speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.77,0:21:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora, move bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.10,0:21:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought of a title.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.10,0:21:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yume, Kibou... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I started studying Japanese recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.37,0:21:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soon, they start thinking that they want \Nto live together the way they used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, their wish reaches \Neverybody's hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.65,0:21:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They acknowledge and forgive each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.84,0:21:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and decide to cooperate and \Nlive together once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.47,0:21:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.73,0:21:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can definitely feel the \Nexcitement on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.62,0:21:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When they free themselves from fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.01,0:21:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's the time \Nthey obtain real freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.53,0:21:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why this story's title is:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Freedom"!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:21:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Mia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is enjoying it. I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.69,0:22:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One day, I'm sure the day \Nwe can hear this applause{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.61,0:22:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with everyone, even all the \Nformer members, will come.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.03,0:22:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.66,0:22:36.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Next Kaleido Star"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.22,0:22:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, apologize to everyone! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.21,0:22:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so, Mia's direction was a \Nbig, big, big success! Yet...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.21,0:22:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because of Yuri's plot... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.51,0:22:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today is Kaleido Stage's last day...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.05,0:22:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Miss Layla, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.13,0:22:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}what on earth are we going to do \Nnow? What on earth? What on earth?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.17,0:22:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next time on Kaleido Star, \N"Yuri's Amazing Trap."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.15,0:23:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My wings are my dream and \Non towards the sky...{\i0}
